forsothe = [[\textbf{Forsothe} - forsooth \phnm{/fəˈsuːθ/ (adv.)}: Archaic. From OE \textit{forsoð} ``indeed, in truth, verily, to tell the truth,'' from for ``for'' + soð ``truth'' (sooth). Regarded as affected in speech by c. 1600.]]

